      </acqinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_6a210ae980ca42455b555d69c4cf5746">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The John Emory Buxton Wells, Class of 1917, Sheffield Scientific School, Yale University, photograph collection consists of six photographs of Wells in group portraits of the St. Elmo society, the St. Elmo Society German dance, in front of the Adee Boathouse, the 1917 Sheffield freshman class, and possibly the Delta Phi fraternity.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
